      "content": "I understand that you need relief and want to prioritize your comfort. However, even small amounts of ibuprofen can have a significant effect on people who are on warfarin, potentially increasing the risk of unwanted bleeding. Although you're used to taking them, doing so without consulting your doctor may pose a risk to your health. It could be helpful to try other safe pain relief methods such as applying a cold pack to your head, staying hydrated, or using a caffeine-containing product like coffee or decaf tea to see if that alleviates your headache. If the pain persists, waiting until Monday to call your healthcare provider would be the most cautious approach to ensure your safety.",
